---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SiteShell from "../components/SiteShell.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Shipping & Returns — Tommy Day Art"
  description="Shipping, preorder, local handoff, return, and damaged package information for Tommy Day Art orders."
  canonicalUrl="/shipping/"
>
  <SiteShell>
    <section class="page-intro-copy">
      <p class="section-eyebrow">Shop policies</p>
      <h1 class="text-2xl font-serif">Shipping & Returns</h1>
      <p>
        Tommy Day Art orders ship from Indianapolis, Indiana. Prints, cards, and flat originals are
        packed flat with care.
      </p>

      <h2>Preorders</h2>
      <p>
        Preorder items are produced after the preorder window closes. The current launch preorder is
        expected to ship around Late June 2026. If timing changes, order updates will be sent by
        email.
      </p>

      <h2>Shipping</h2>
      <p>
        Shipping options and rates are shown at checkout. Orders that contain preorder items may ship
        together when the preorder batch is ready.
      </p>

      <h2>Local handoff</h2>
      <p>
        If you know Tommy in real life, a local handoff / pickup option may be available at checkout.
        Use that option only if you can coordinate pickup in or around Indianapolis.
      </p>

      <h2>Returns and exchanges</h2>
      <p>
        Because originals, prints, cards, and preorder goods are small-batch items, returns and
        exchanges are handled case by case. If something arrives damaged or incorrect, email
        <a href="mailto:hey@tommyday.com">hey@tommyday.com</a> within 7 days of delivery.
      </p>

      <h2>Damaged packages</h2>
      <p>
        Keep the packaging and send photos of the damage, the package, and the item. That makes it
        much easier to sort out a replacement, refund, or carrier claim.
      </p>
    </section>
  </SiteShell>
</BaseLayout>
